Optional Rule: Custom Standing Stone (Point-Buy)
For players who have a specific character concept in mind that no Standing Stone quite captures, this optional rule allows full customization of your starting stats at the cost of your Stone Benefit.
The Rules:
You have 40 points to distribute freely across your four stats: Might, Agility, Magic, and Guile.
No single stat may exceed 20.
No single stat may fall below 4.
You receive no Standing Stone Benefit. The unique ability listed on every Stone is part of what you give up for full creative control.
You still choose a Race and receive its stat bonus normally.
You still choose your Skills and calculate your HP and FP as normal.
A Word of Warning:
Putting 20 in a single stat is not as powerful as it sounds. Difficulty modifiers can still punish even your best rolls, and the points you spend reaching 20 in one stat will leave your remaining three stats painfully low. A character built this way will be exceptional at one thing and genuinely helpless at almost everything else. That is a valid and interesting character concept ΓÇö just go in with open eyes.
When to Use This:
The thirteen Standing Stones are designed to cover every major archetype in Skyrim. If you look at them and one fits your concept, take it ΓÇö the Stone Benefit is genuinely powerful and you will miss it. Point-buy exists for the player who has already decided exactly who their character is and wants their numbers to reflect that.


