Utility Overhaul: Sneak
The art of remaining unseen, striking from the shadows, and moving like a ghost.
Core Mechanic: The Hidden State
Being Hidden: You are Hidden when you succeed on an Agility Roll to move unseen.
The Benefit: While Hidden, enemies cannot target you.
The Strike: An attack made while Hidden has Advantage.
Breaking Stealth: You lose the Hidden status immediately after you attack, cast a spell, or if an enemy succeeds on a Guile roll to find you.
The Sneak Skill Tree
Governing Stat: Agility
Novice: You can attempt to become Hidden as a Minor Action by making an Agility Roll.
Apprentice: Silent Roll (Evasion & Awareness)
Combat (Reaction): When an enemy detects you, you may use your Reaction and spend 3 FP to immediately move to a new location and make a new Agility Roll. If successful, you remain Hidden.
Utility (Vigilant): While you are Hidden, your senses are heightened. You have Advantage on all Guile rolls to spot enemies, traps, or hidden doors. You are the eyes of the party.
Adept: Deadly Aim (Assassination & Safety)
Combat (Lethality): Any successful attack made while Hidden is automatically a Critical Success.
Note: Per weapon properties, Daggers deal triple (x3) damage on a Sneak Attack Critical.


Utility (Light Foot): You do not trigger pressure plates or tripwires while Sneaking. You can safely scout dangerous hallways and disable mechanisms without risk.
Expert: Shadow Warrior (Combat Stealth & Sabotage)
Combat (Vanish): As a Minor Action, you can spend 6 FP to make an Agility Roll to become Hidden, even if you are currently being observed by an enemy.
Utility (Ghost Hand): You can interact with the environment without revealing your position. Picking a lock, opening a door, looting a chest, or pulling a lever does not break your Hidden status, provided you do not attack.
Master: Invisibility 
Active Ability: Once per combat (or scene), you can spend 15 FP to become Invisible for 3 rounds.
Combat Benefit: You are automatically Hidden even in plain sight. Attacking breaks invisibility.
Utility Benefit: While Invisible, you are undetectable by nonmagical sensors or scent. You leave no footprints and make no sound, allowing you to bypass even magical defenses.
