Character Progression: Forging Your Legend
Your legend is not forged in a single day. As you complete perilous adventures and overcome great challenges, your skills will sharpen and your power will grow. This system uses a milestone-based progression. Instead of tracking experience points, you earn Advancement Points (AP) for completing your objectives.
Earning Advancement Points
The path to power is simple: succeed. At the end of a successful adventure, every player gains 1 Advancement Point. You can spend your AP immediately or save it for more expensive upgrades.
Dragon Kills (standing rule — dragons are always worth more): a regular dragon awards 2 AP to whoever lands the killing blow and 1 AP to every other participant. An elder dragon awards 4 AP for the killing blow and 2 AP for participation.
The Tiers of Play
Your total AP determines your Tier — the scale of legend your deeds have reached:
Novice (0-3 AP) - Apprentice (3-6 AP) - Adept (6-9 AP) - Expert (9-15 AP) - Master (15-25 AP) - Mythic (25+ AP).
Mythic has no upper limit. The full AP tree (every skill Mastered, every stat at cap) buys out around 181 AP — a horizon, not a destination.
Spending Advancement Points
You can spend your accumulated AP on any of the options from the list below. This is how you customize your hero's growth, choosing to deepen your specializations or broaden your talents.
