Stat Increase: Increase one of your four core Stat Scores by 1. A stat cannot be raised above 18 by this method. (This is a major, long-term investment).


Special Progression Paths
Characters who dedicate themselves to mastering either the arcane or martial disciplines unlock unique benefits as their power grows. These benefits trigger when you spend AP to advance a relevant skill; they do not apply during initial character creation.
Combat Prowess
A warrior's focused dedication to their combat style hones their body and instincts to a razor's edge.
The Adept Benefit: When you first reach the Adept tier in any Combat Skill (One-Handed, Two-Handed, Archery), your body becomes tougher. You gain a permanent +2 bonus to your maximum HP.
The Expert Benefit: When you first reach the Expert tier in any Combat Skill, your stamina becomes legendary. You gain a permanent +2 bonus to your maximum FP.
The Master Benefit: When you first reach the Master tier in any Combat Skill, you have achieved true mastery of the battlefield. You may choose one other Combat or Armor skill where you are an Apprentice. That skill is immediately promoted to Adept for free.
Arcane Studies
A mage's focused study in one school of magic naturally unlocks a basic understanding of others. The free promotions granted by this rule cannot advance a skill beyond the Adept tier.
The Adept Benefit: When you first reach the Adept tier in any magic skill, you may choose one of your Novice magic skills. That skill is immediately promoted to Apprentice for free.
The Expert Benefit: When you first reach the Expert tier in any magic skill, you may choose one of your Apprentice magic skills. That skill is immediately promoted to Adept for free.
The Master Benefit: When you first reach the Master tier in any magic skill, you may choose another one of your Apprentice magic skills. That skill is immediately promoted to Adept for free.

The Master's Form - Forging Your Signature Technique
As your mastery of combat grows, you learn to express your will through steel. This system allows you to create a signature combat technique that is uniquely yoursΓÇöa move that evolves and gains new facets as you achieve new heights of martial prowess.
The Creation Process
All techniques are built over time, gaining power at each new tier of martial skill: Adept, Expert, and Master.
I. The Foundation (Adept Tier)
Your journey begins when you first reach Adept Tier in any Combat Skill (One-Handed, Two-Handed, or Archery). This skill becomes the technique's Primary Skill.
1. Choose Your Martial Style:
Your technique's core concept determines its Governing Stat. This choice is permanent and unlocks a unique list of Effects that you can purchase.
The Style of Might (Governed by Might): Techniques of overwhelming power, brute force, and heavy impact. You break guards, shatter armor, and send foes flying.
The Style of Agility (Governed by Agility): Techniques of blinding speed, precision, and fluid movement. You bleed foes with a dozen cuts, bypass their defenses, and are never where they expect you to be.
The Style of Guile (Governed by Guile): Techniques of cunning feints, tactical exploitation, and psychological warfare. You turn your opponent's strength against them and control the flow of battle.
2. Build Your "Budget":
At this first stage of creation, you gain a "budget" to build your technique. You must choose one of the following budget options:
Option A: Select ONE Major Drawback to unlock ONE Major Effect.
Option B: Select TWO Minor Drawbacks to unlock TWO Minor Effects.
You can choose from the Universal Drawback list or the list specific to your chosen Martial Style.
II. The Evolution (Expert and Master Tiers)
Your technique grows with you. Each time you reach a new milestone, you gain a new budget of drawbacks to add more effects. The choices you make at each tier are permanent additions; your final technique is the cumulative total of all Drawbacks and Effects you have selected.
Reaching Expert Tier in your technique's Primary Skill: You gain another budget. You may add one Major Drawback OR two Minor Drawbacks to your technique to unlock the corresponding number of new Effects from your chosen Style's list.
Reaching Master Tier in your technique's Primary Skill: You gain your final budget, adding one Major Drawback OR two Minor Drawbacks to unlock the final Effects for your technique.
Diversifying Your Training: Each time you reach Adept Tier in a different Combat Skill, you may add one Minor Drawback (Universal or Style-Specific) to unlock one additional Minor Effect from your Style.
Mastery of Defense: Each time you reach Expert Tier in an Armor Skill (Heavy or Light), you may add one Minor Drawback (Universal or Style-Specific) to unlock one additional Minor Effect (Universal or Style-Specific).

