Advanced Magic: The Art of Dual Casting


Dual Casting allows a mage to weave two spells together into a single release.
The Golden Rule: Proficiency Over Power
To weave two spells together, you must have mastered the basics of that tier. You must be one Skill Tier higher than the spell you wish to Dual Cast.
Novice Spells: Requires Apprentice Skill.
Apprentice Spells: Requires Adept Skill.
Adept Spells: Requires Expert Skill.
Expert Spells: Requires Master Skill.
Master Spells: Impossible to Dual Cast via normal means.
Method 1: The Standard Dual Cast (Immediate Release)


This sacrifices mobility for raw magical output in a single turn.
Cost: Pay the combined FP cost of both spells immediately.
Action: This consumes your Major Action AND your Minor Action. You cannot move, dodge, or drink a potion.
Effect:
Resonance (Same Spell x2): The spell deals Double Damage or has Double Duration.
Fusion (Two Different Spells): Both spell effects apply to the target simultaneously.
Method 2: The Infinite Overcharge (The Living Bomb)


A mage may choose to hold a Dual Cast spell, feeding more magicka into the weave turn after turn. There is no limit to how long this can be held, but the mage becomes a walking powder keg.
The Ritual:
Turn 1: Pay the combined FP cost. Spend Major and Minor actions. You do not release the spell. You are now Charging.
Subsequent Turns: You must spend your Major Action and Minor action to maintain the hold. For every full turn you hold the spell, the Multiplier increases by +1. When you are ready, you must spend your Minor action to release the spell.
Turn 1 (Cast): Base Dual Cast (2x Damage).
Turn 2 (Hold): 3x Damage + Impact (Stagger).
Turn 3 (Hold): 4x Damage + Impact.
Turn 4 (Hold): 5x Damage + Impact... (Infinite Scaling).
The Vulnerability: Absolute Focus
While Charging, you cannot move, cast other spells, or use Reactions. You are completely reliant on your allies to protect you.
Catastrophic Failure: If you take ANY damage (even 1 point) while Charging, concentration breaks immediately. There is no Saving Throw.
The Detonation: The spell explodes centered on you. You take the full, accumulated damage/effect of the spell you were building. If the spell had a status effect (Paralyze, Fear), it applies to you.
Item Synergy: Catalysts
A mage may use items to facilitate a Dual Cast, but the rules for interaction are strict. Item synergy dual casts MAY NOT BE CHARGED.
1. Staves (Resonance Only)
Staves are rigid tools; they cannot be woven into complex new patterns.
Restriction: You can only Dual Cast with a staff if the spell in your hand matches the spell in the staff (e.g., Staff of Fireballs + Fireball spell).
Effect: This counts as Resonance. You gain Double Damage/Effect.
Cost: You pay FP for the hand-cast spell only. The Staff loses a charge.
2. Scrolls (The Forbidden Loophole)
Scrolls contain completed magical formulas written by ancient masters. They are the only way to bypass the "Skill Tier" limit.
The Mechanic: You cast a spell from one hand and read a matching Scroll with the other.
The Master Exception: This is the only way to Dual Cast a Master Spell. If you are a Master of Destruction, you can cast Fire Storm (18 FP, per the Spell List) and read a Scroll of Fire Storm simultaneously.
Cost: FP for the spell + The Scroll is destroyed.
Effect: Resonance. The effects are doubled. (Note: A Dual Cast Master Spell is a city-leveling event).
