Advanced Magic: Arcane Augmentation
The Art of Upcasting
While Dual Casting allows a mage to double their output by using both hands, Augmentation is the subtle art of forcing more magicka into a single spell frame than it was designed to hold. It is inefficient and dangerous, but it allows a skilled mage to turn a simple flame into an inferno without sacrificing their mobility.
The Golden Rule: The Proficiency Tax
To Augment a spell, you must cast it with the power of a higher Skill Tier. You must actually know how to cast spells of that higher tier to attempt this.
Example: You cannot force a Novice spell to hit with Expert power unless you are actually an Expert in that school.
The Cost of Power
Augmentation is expensive. You pay the standard cost of the target tier, plus a "tax" of 1 FP for every step up you take.
