Rest & Recovery: Catching Your Breath
Even the mightiest heroes need to rest. When the fight is over and the dungeon is quiet, you have two ways to recover your strength.
Short Rest
A Short Rest is a quick, one-hour pause to bind your wounds and refocus your mind.
Benefit: At the end of a Short Rest, you regain half of your maximum HP and FP, rounded down. You may also perform minor tasks like field repairing sundered armor.
The Risk: Resting in a dangerous, unsecured location is a gamble. Your GM will know if your chosen resting spot is safe. If it isn't, your rest might be interrupted by wandering monsters or other threats, and you will gain no benefits. Choose your resting spots wisely.
Long Rest
A Long Rest is a full night (at least 8 hours) of proper, uninterrupted sleep in a safe and secure location.
Benefit: At the end of a Long Rest, you regain all of your lost HP and FP. Any of your "once per adventure" abilities are also refreshed and ready to use again.
Requirement: You can only take a Long Rest in a Secure Location, such as a room you've rented at an inn, a friendly NPC's home, or a dungeon you have completely cleared of all dangers. You cannot take a Long Rest in the middle of a dangerous, unexplored area.

Status Effects Explained
This list defines the common status effects that can be inflicted on characters and enemies during an adventure.
Bleeding
A creature that is Bleeding takes damage at the start of their turn. This effect Stacks Intensity. If a creature is hit multiple times by a Bleed-causing weapon, the damage numbers are added together (e.g., 3 hits for 1 bleed each = 3 damage at the start of their turn). 
Calm
A creature that is Calm becomes non-hostile for the duration of the effect. They will not initiate attacks or take aggressive actions. The effect typically ends if the creature is attacked.
Encased
The target is completely trapped. While encased, they are immune to all damage but cannot take any actions. This effect lasts for a set number of rounds.
Fear
A creature affected by Fear is terrified and must spend their turn moving away from the source of the fear by the safest available route.
Frenzy
A creature in a Frenzy is overcome with rage and must use their turn to attack the nearest creature, whether it is a friend or foe.
Invisible
A creature that is Invisible cannot be seen by normal means. This effect lasts for a set duration or ends immediately if the creature attacks, or takes any hostile action.
Paralyzed
The target is completely immobilized and helpless. They cannot perform a Major Action, a Minor Action, or move on their turn.
Slowed
The target's movements or reaction times are hindered. They lose their next Minor Action.
Staggered
The target is thrown off-balance by a powerful blow or effect. They lose their next Major Action.

Example Character: A Legend in the Making
Let's see how all these steps come together to create a complete character. We'll build Kaelen, the Breton Knight.
Step 1: Choose Your Race
Kaelen is a Breton, known for her people's innate connection to the arcane.
Stat Bonus: +1 to her final Magic score.
Racial Ability: Dragonskin (Once per adventure, take half damage from a hostile spell).

Step 2: Choose Your Standing Stone
She was born under The Lord stone, destined for a life of resilience and command.
Base Stats: Might 15, Agility 8, Magic 6, Guile 11.
Applying Racial Bonus: Her Magic score increases by 1.
Final Stats: Might 15, Agility 8, Magic 7, Guile 11.
Stone Benefit: Knight's Ward (+1 to her armor's Damage Reduction, and once per adventure she can re-roll a failed roll against a spell).

Step 3: Choose Skills & Perks
Kaelen's training makes her a formidable, front-line warrior. To match her chosen gear, she focuses on two-handed combat.
Adept Skill: Two-Handed (Adept Perk: Devastating Charge)
Apprentice Skills: Heavy Armor (Apprentice Perk: Well Fitted), Restoration (Apprentice Perk: Respite), and Speech (Apprentice Perk: Persuasion).

Step 4: Calculate Resources
Kaelen's stats and perks determine her survivability.
Health (HP): The formula is 8 + (Might / 4). For Kaelen, that's 8 + (15 / 4 = 3) = 11 HP. Her Well Fitted perk from Heavy Armor adds +2, for a final total of 13 HP.
Focus Points (FP): The formula is (Agility / 2) + (Magic / 2). For Kaelen, that's (8 / 2) + (7 / 2 = 3) = 4 + 3 = 7 FP.

Step 5: Gear Up!
Kaelen is a warrior through and through, so she takes The Warrior's Kit.
Weapon: Steel Greatsword 
Armor: Steel Armor
Consumable: Potion of Minor Healing
Coin: 25 Gold
She also receives the Standard Adventurer's Pack.


